sql:
SELECT cycle_id, total_failures_in_cycle
FROM test_cycles
ORDER BY total_failures_in_cycle DESC;

SELECT cycle_id, COUNT(test_id) AS number_of_tests
FROM test_results
GROUP BY cycle_id;

SELECT cycle_id, num_testsuite, total_failures_in_cycle
FROM test_cycles
ORDER BY total_failures_in_cycle DESC;

external_knowledge:
External knowledge:
- A sub-cycle is a test cycle that is a subset of another test cycle; 
- Optimal failures and execution times are the expected number of failures and execution times for a given threshold, respectively; 
- Actual failures and execution times are the actual number of failures and execution times recorded, respectively; 
- Thresholds (25%, 50%, 75%) refer to the percentage of test suites executed; 
- Cumulative execution time is the total execution time of all test cycles up to a given point in time.
